# HTML5
> opinionated HTML5 reference

- [Accessibility][Introduction to Web Accessibility] unlocking [attributes][Attributes] are always required.

## **Table of Contents**

- [`<html>` bootstrap](#html-bootstrap)
- [`<img>` element](#img-element)

## `<html>` bootstrap
> **[Minimal][Anatomy of a HTML document] HTML5 bootstrap.**
```
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <title>Minimal HTML5 bootstrap</title>
</head>
<body></body>
</html>
```

## [`<img>`][] element
> **required [attributes][`<img>` attributes]**: `src`, [`alt`][An alt Decision Tree]

### `<img>` element + `alt` attribute
<img src="img/the-truth-shall-set-you-free.jpg" alt="(John 8:32) Then you will know the truth, and the truth will set you free"/>

```
<img src="img/the-truth-shall-set-you-free.jpg" alt="(John 8:32) Then you will know the truth, and the truth will set you free"/>
```

### `<img>` with in-line [base64][Base64] image `src` attribute
> **format**: [`data:[<media type>][;base64],<data>`][Data URI scheme]

<img src="img/the-truth-shall-set-you-free.jpg" alt="(John 8:32) Then you will know the truth, and the truth will set you free"/>

```
<img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="(John 8:32) Then you will know the truth, and the truth will set you free"/>
```

###### [Base64] encode image

```
cat img/the-truth-shall-set-you-free.jpg | base64 | pbcopy
```
